and tells us how to use
it and what it will do.

00:23:34.166 --> 00:23:36.566 A:middle
Great! Just a few lines of
code and we were able to clean

00:23:36.566 --> 00:23:38.776 A:middle
up the app and make
it pretty accessible.

00:23:39.276 --> 00:23:40.386 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: VoiceOver off.

00:23:40.736 --> 00:23:43.456 A:middle
&gt;&gt; IAN FISCH: So where
did we get so far?

00:23:43.806 --> 00:23:45.516 A:middle
The earthquake cell
is now accessible,

00:23:45.516 --> 00:23:46.626 A:middle
we are not communicating
anything

00:23:46.626 --> 00:23:48.976 A:middle
with text color anymore,
which is really great,

00:23:48.976 --> 00:23:50.656 A:middle
that ugly yellow
is finally gone.

00:23:51.246 --> 00:23:53.576 A:middle
The map detail view now
has meaningful traits

00:23:53.576 --> 00:23:55.016 A:middle
on those labels so it's clear

00:23:55.016 --> 00:23:57.446 A:middle
to the VoiceOver user what's
happening and they can navigate

00:23:57.476 --> 00:23:58.446 A:middle
by headings if they like.

00:23:59.026 --> 00:24:00.836 A:middle
That Info button it accessible.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:59.026 --> 00:24:00.836 A:middle
That Info button it accessible.

00:24:01.076 --> 00:24:05.286 A:middle
We still need a way to add
something to the favorite list,

00:24:06.066 --> 00:24:09.366 A:middle
and the favorite graph
is still inaccessible.

00:24:10.316 --> 00:24:14.566 A:middle
How would we make
this graph accessible?

00:24:15.596 --> 00:24:17.916 A:middle
So let's start by going back

00:24:17.916 --> 00:24:19.706 A:middle
to those questions we were
talking about earlier.

00:24:19.916 --> 00:24:21.476 A:middle
The first one was:
Do I serve a purpose?

00:24:21.536 --> 00:24:24.666 A:middle
So there is a lot of
information being communicated

00:24:24.666 --> 00:24:29.016 A:middle
in this graph, but not all of
it is really serving a purpose

00:24:29.016 --> 00:24:30.186 A:middle
or really important to the user.

00:24:30.186 --> 00:24:32.226 A:middle
So what's the most
important bits in this graph?

00:24:32.226 --> 00:24:34.366 A:middle
I think that's the points,

00:24:34.796 --> 00:24:36.876 A:middle
because they tell us exactly
what we are comparing,

00:24:37.046 --> 00:24:39.376 A:middle
so that's probably what
we should make accessible.

00:24:40.666 --> 00:24:43.316 A:middle
The next question that's worth
talking about is: Where am I?

00:24:43.676 --> 00:24:45.866 A:middle
So what do we set for
the accessibility frame

00:24:46.026 --> 00:24:46.656 A:middle
for these points?

00:24:47.866 --> 00:24:50.596 A:middle
So you might think
that the orange boxes

00:24:50.596 --> 00:24:55.696 A:middle
that you see now are a
good idea, but if you look

00:24:55.696 --> 00:24:59.066 A:middle
at the view as a whole,
most of it isn't accessible.

00:24:59.946 --> 00:25:03.806 A:middle
So most of it is
just dead space,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:59.946 --> 00:25:03.806 A:middle
So most of it is
just dead space,

00:25:04.216 --> 00:25:06.846 A:middle
and so as a VoiceOver
user slides their finger

00:25:06.846 --> 00:25:09.526 A:middle
around the screen to search for
points, it will be mostly empty.

00:25:10.236 --> 00:25:13.456 A:middle
A better frame might
be something like this.

00:25:13.946 --> 00:25:16.626 A:middle
So a VoiceOver user can
slide his or her finger

00:25:16.626 --> 00:25:18.416 A:middle
across the screen,
and they will hit all

00:25:18.416 --> 00:25:19.496 A:middle
of the points as they do so.

00:25:19.496 --> 00:25:22.316 A:middle
And then as long as we set
the accessibility value

00:25:22.316 --> 00:25:24.616 A:middle
to the magnitude, we
haven't lost anything.

00:25:24.616 --> 00:25:26.446 A:middle
We haven't lost any information.

00:25:26.766 --> 00:25:28.556 A:middle
So that seems like a good plan.

00:25:29.456 --> 00:25:30.896 A:middle
Unfortunately, I happen to know

00:25:30.896 --> 00:25:33.976 A:middle
that the graph view
is just one big view,

00:25:33.976 --> 00:25:36.296 A:middle
and everything is drawn
directly into the view.

00:25:36.696 --> 00:25:42.056 A:middle
So how do we make one view
accessible into multiple parts?

00:25:42.896 --> 00:25:45.406 A:middle
And the good news is we have
got an API for that as well,

00:25:45.406 --> 00:25:47.176 A:middle
UIAccessibility element.

00:25:47.236 --> 00:25:51.286 A:middle
So this is a great way to
create specific objects just

00:25:51.286 --> 00:25:54.416 A:middle
for accessibility to break
up a view into subelements

00:25:54.816 --> 00:25:57.186 A:middle
and still answer those great
six questions we have been

00:25:57.186 --> 00:25:57.826 A:middle
talking about.

00:25:58.486 --> 00:26:01.266 A:middle
The only new part is the
accessibility container,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:25:58.486 --> 00:26:01.266 A:middle
The only new part is the
accessibility container,

00:26:01.266 --> 00:26:03.136 A:middle
which you would just set
to the containing view.

00:26:04.106 --> 00:26:07.616 A:middle
Great! So with this API, we
can make the graph accessible.

00:26:08.216 --> 00:26:10.506 A:middle
How do we add something
to that favorite list

00:26:10.816 --> 00:26:12.686 A:middle
so there is something
to display on the graph?

00:26:13.276 --> 00:26:17.036 A:middle
For that I think we should use
Accessibility Perform Magic Tap,

00:26:17.626 --> 00:26:18.716 A:middle
which is this really cool API

00:26:18.716 --> 00:26:21.626 A:middle
to just do the right thing
in the right context.

00:26:22.416 --> 00:26:24.436 A:middle
A good example of that is

00:26:24.516 --> 00:26:26.096 A:middle
when a VoiceOver user
gets a phone call,

00:26:26.306 --> 00:26:29.666 A:middle
they can do the Magic Tap
gesture, which is two fingers,

00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:32.776 A:middle
double-tap on the screen, and
that will do the magic thing,

00:26:32.866 --> 00:26:34.576 A:middle
which is answer the phone call.

00:26:35.406 --> 00:26:38.496 A:middle
So that will allow us to add
something to the favorite list,

00:26:39.446 --> 00:26:41.376 A:middle
but what do we add to the list?

00:26:42.256 --> 00:26:44.046 A:middle
And for that we can
use some brand-new API

00:26:44.206 --> 00:26:46.846 A:middle
in iOS 9 called Accessibility
Focus.

00:26:46.956 --> 00:26:50.256 A:middle
This will allow you to get
the currently focused element

00:26:50.436 --> 00:26:51.956 A:middle
for a given assistive technology

00:26:52.256 --> 00:26:53.726 A:middle
like VoiceOver or
Switch Control.

00:26:54.436 --> 00:26:56.486 A:middle
If you are interested in
tracking focus as it moves

00:26:56.486 --> 00:26:59.196 A:middle
around your app, we
provide a notification

00:26:59.536 --> 00:27:02.216 A:middle
that will tell you the
currently focused element

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:26:59.536 --> 00:27:02.216 A:middle
that will tell you the
currently focused element

00:27:02.406 --> 00:27:03.706 A:middle
and the previously
focused element

00:27:03.706 --> 00:27:05.086 A:middle
for a given assistive
technology.

00:27:05.796 --> 00:27:08.356 A:middle
We know what to add
to the favorites list,

00:27:08.356 --> 00:27:11.186 A:middle
we know how to add it, and
then we can explore the graph.

00:27:11.496 --> 00:27:14.596 A:middle
So let's look at
implementing that now.

00:27:20.116 --> 00:27:20.546 A:middle
All right.

00:27:20.626 --> 00:27:22.036 A:middle
Back in Xcode.

00:27:23.096 --> 00:27:26.986 A:middle
So let's add something
to the favorite list.

00:27:27.986 --> 00:27:29.576 A:middle
So if we go to the app delegate,

00:27:30.746 --> 00:27:35.956 A:middle
we can add Accessibility
Perform Magic Tap.

00:27:36.266 --> 00:27:39.526 A:middle
So we will grab the currently
focused element for VoiceOver,

00:27:40.366 --> 00:27:43.246 A:middle
check if that element
responds to toggle favorite,

00:27:43.276 --> 00:27:46.286 A:middle
like the cell, and if it
does, we will ask it to toggle

00:27:46.286 --> 00:27:47.696 A:middle
as favorite and then return Yes.

00:27:48.206 --> 00:27:49.506 A:middle
Otherwise, we return No,

00:27:49.946 --> 00:27:52.416 A:middle
and VoiceOver will do the
next-most-magical thing

00:27:52.566 --> 00:27:54.356 A:middle
in that context,
whatever that may be.

00:27:54.856 --> 00:27:59.186 A:middle
So that will allow us to add
something to the favorite list.

00:27:59.616 --> 00:28:01.456 A:middle
Now, let's look at the graph.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:27:59.616 --> 00:28:01.456 A:middle
Now, let's look at the graph.

00:28:02.556 --> 00:28:03.716 A:middle
All right.

00:28:03.766 --> 00:28:07.096 A:middle
So it looks like I'm
drawing it with CAShapeLayer,

00:28:07.236 --> 00:28:09.526 A:middle
which is a great way to draw
a graph, but not a great way

00:28:09.526 --> 00:28:11.586 A:middle
to draw an accessible graph.

00:28:11.836 --> 00:28:15.456 A:middle
So down here I'm actually
grabbing the point

00:28:15.596 --> 00:28:16.966 A:middle
and drawing it.

00:28:17.616 --> 00:28:19.056 A:middle
So that seems like a good place

00:28:19.096 --> 00:28:22.366 A:middle
to create my UIAccessibility
element.

00:28:23.946 --> 00:28:28.376 A:middle
So I create a UIAccessibility
element, setting its container

00:28:28.376 --> 00:28:30.096 A:middle
to Self, the graph view.

00:28:30.146 --> 00:28:35.186 A:middle
And then I set its label to a
formatted version of the date.

00:28:35.816 --> 00:28:37.336 A:middle
So we know when it happened.

00:28:37.846 --> 00:28:40.456 A:middle
We will set the value to
the magnitude description.

00:28:40.966 --> 00:28:42.146 A:middle
That's good.

00:28:42.266 --> 00:28:45.976 A:middle
And then like we talked about,
I will take the frame and set it

00:28:45.976 --> 00:28:49.216 A:middle
to slightly wider
than the point,

00:28:49.746 --> 00:28:51.756 A:middle
and the full height
of the graph.

00:28:51.756 --> 00:28:56.226 A:middle
I will set that as the
frame after converting it

00:28:56.306 --> 00:28:57.676 A:middle
to screen coordinates.

00:28:58.496 --> 00:29:03.576 A:middle
And finally add that to
an array that I had ready,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:58.496 --> 00:29:03.576 A:middle
And finally add that to
an array that I had ready,

00:29:03.976 --> 00:29:06.396 A:middle
and set that as the
accessibility elements

00:29:06.756 --> 00:29:07.436 A:middle
for the graph view.

00:29:08.456 --> 00:29:10.396 A:middle
So just a few more
lines of code.

00:29:10.936 --> 00:29:12.976 A:middle
Let's see what that looks like.

00:29:18.516 --> 00:29:19.066 A:middle
All right.

00:29:19.116 --> 00:29:22.066 A:middle
So I will triple-tap
Home and start VoiceOver.

00:29:22.196 --> 00:29:22.816 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: VoiceOver on.

00:29:23.136 --> 00:29:25.096 A:middle
FaceTime, QuakeWatch.

00:29:25.936 --> 00:29:26.826 A:middle
Double-tap to open.

00:29:26.826 --> 00:29:27.316 A:middle
QuakeWatch.

00:29:27.616 --> 00:29:28.646 A:middle
Earthquakes, heading.

00:29:28.936 --> 00:29:30.086 A:middle
&gt;&gt; IAN FISCH: There's
those beautiful cells.

00:29:30.086 --> 00:29:33.386 A:middle
I will do the Magic Tap
gesture, which is two fingers,

00:29:33.386 --> 00:29:34.566 A:middle
double-tap on the screen.

00:29:35.276 --> 00:29:39.196 A:middle
And there it is,
now it's a favorite.

00:29:39.386 --> 00:29:40.476 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: 12 kilometers.

00:29:40.726 --> 00:29:43.926 A:middle
California 2015.

00:29:44.096 --> 00:29:46.116 A:middle
11:10 a.m. Favorite.

00:29:46.496 --> 00:29:47.546 A:middle
&gt;&gt; IAN FISCH: It
says it's a favorite.

00:29:47.646 --> 00:29:48.586 A:middle
That's good.

00:29:49.106 --> 00:29:50.026 A:middle
So let's add a few more.

00:29:51.356 --> 00:29:54.196 A:middle
First, we have to wait
for earthquakes to happen.

00:29:54.196 --> 00:29:55.186 A:middle
All right.

00:29:55.856 --> 00:29:57.786 A:middle
Three should be enough.

00:29:58.906 --> 00:30:00.206 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: Detail,
back button.

